<reference id="no-topic-nesting" xml:lang="en-us">
   <title>
      <keyword>no-topic-nesting</keyword>
   </title>
   <shortdesc>The &lt;<keyword>no-topic-nesting</keyword>&gt; element is a placeholder in the
DITA architecture. It is not actually used by the DITA DTDs; it is for use
only when creating a customized DTD where the information designer wants to
eliminate the ability to nest topics. <b>Not for use by authors.</b>
   
   
